From 8dcee9aad70d501332dc957c179702260592ad1a Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Codex <codex@localhost>
Date: Fri, 17 Jul 2026 18:55:24 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] drm/nouveau/nv50: restore legacy GPFIFO path for pre-Fermi
 A/B

The v6.16 "drm/nouveau/nv50-: separate CHANNEL_GPFIFO handling out
from CHANNEL_DMA" change moved NV50-and-later GPFIFO submission from
nouveau_dma into nvif/chan.  It also made userspace segments
subroutines, moved main-push progress tracking to TOP_LEVEL_GET, and
removed the old explicit push-buffer readback flush.

Keep the modern nvif channel implementation for Fermi and later, where
subsequent semaphore-progress changes depend on it.  For NV50, G8x, and
GT2xx channels only, restore the legacy IB accounting, submission,
progress tracking, and BAR flush while retaining the surrounding 6.18
driver.

This is a narrowly scoped diagnostic A/B patch for an NVA5 regression.
It is not a claim that the channel split is conclusively faulty on all
pre-Fermi hardware.

Link: https://git.kernel.org/linus/d1fb887a08d8a21284e9a4be476f103353a32e7a
Signed-off-by: Codex <codex@localhost>
